ation**: Uses Provider pattern so nested elements stay in sync with the frame"},"307":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-18","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#features","content":"**Field wrapper composition**: Designed to sit inside TextField, NumberField, DateField, or Select as the main field UI"},"308":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-19","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#props","content":"FieldFrame accepts the following props:"},"309":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-20","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#basic-example","content":"Examples for leading control, trailing control, and icon accessories are in Examples at the end."},"310":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-21","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"FieldFrame renders a single React Aria `Provider` that supplies the necessary context to its children. Structure tree:"},"311":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-22","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"The following list describes the internal React Aria components used to compose FieldFrame:"},"312":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-23","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**Label** (optional) — Rendered when `label` is provided. Shows a required indicator (asterisk)."},"313":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-24","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**Group** — The visual frame. Exposes `data-focus-within`, `data-focus-visible`, `data-disabled`, and `data-invalid`. All foc